  "title": "Avionics Engineer (A112)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Industry: </strong>Aerospace / Aviation Sector</p><p><strong>Address: </strong>Central area</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Position Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>The role will focus on aerospace / avionics systems for aviation aircraft.</li><li>Handle review, project life cycle, feasibility evaluation and system requirements, design to integration and troubleshooting.</li><li>Will also performance testing, user training and education.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Position Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Must be a Bachelors' Degree in Electrical and Electronics Engineering, Aerospace / Aviation with focus on airborne electronic systems and navigations theory and course curriculum.</li><li>Fresh graduate are welcome to apply.</li><li>Experience and Theoretical knowledge in communciations, navigation systems and avionics I/O interfaces.</li><li>Comfortable working in a technical environment with sophisticated equipment.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Thank you!</p><p><br /></p><p>Joseph Syho</p><p><br /></p><p>R1108657</p><p><br /></p><p>18C9079</p>",
